The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 Calcutta Municipal Corporation, in association with the CAB, will organise a Twenty20 tournament. Christened the Kolkata Premier League (KPL), the meet will feature 15 teams (boroughs) divided into groups of four. Starting from April 8, 28 matches will be spread over a period 13 days with the final on April 21. The matches will be held at Deshapriya Park and Deshbandhu Park.                
	 Raiganj S.C defeated Baul Sporting Association 3-0 in a group A match of the Officers Choice State League in Dakshin Dinajpur on Friday. Palash Mardi, Madan Hansda and Sagar Giri scored for the winners.                
	 Noted table tennis coach Tarun Mukherjee, 42, passed away on Thursday night at a city hospital. Mukherjee was involved with the BTTA coaching school. Some of his wards include Poulami Ghatak and Somali Sarkar among others.                
	BASKETBALL: Inter-school meet, matches at the Loreto House courts from 2pm.                                                                                                                                                                       
